values.PreceptorAssociated3: Yes, a lot.  They don't feel our students are prepared.  They stated that they know we are a high-quality institution but recommend that our admissions processes be such that we don't only look at grades.  With further questioning they revealed that they have had a couple students that caused their CIs to state they would no longer take WashU students, and have only done so because they wanted to help us when we were in a bind (ad hocs).  They then stated they believe this is because they were international students and perhaps it was communication and culture, but they felt they were unprofessional.  One example was that one would fall asleep while at the CE.  When asked if this was ever reported to us they stated that they didn't think so but they weren't their students.  They reiterated that the current student has been "lovely."
values.PreceptorAssociatedB: Proceed with caution.  The comments from the SCCE and CI were concerning, as was the fact that they apparently do not want to take our students anymore but have not reached out to discuss.  The current student has had a generally positive experience, but they seem to have a bias again international students.
